message.content: It is difficult to provide an accurate summary of what most women in Papua New Guinea think of abortion, as opinions on this topic can vary among individuals. However, it is worth noting that Papua New Guinea is a predominantly Christian country, and religious beliefs often influence attitudes towards abortion. Christianity generally opposes abortion, considering it morally wrong. Additionally, cultural and societal factors may also play a role in shaping opinions on this issue. It is important to recognize that there may be diverse perspectives among women in Papua New Guinea, and individual opinions may differ from the general trends.
